We might just be listening to a new album from the Iconic singer, Sade Adu. Rated R & B stated that this revelation was made by her collaborator Stuart Matthewman. Adu has been on a hiatus after her album Soldier of Love dropped in 2010. It was not until Disney’s A Wrinkle In Time where she sang Flowers in the Universe, did we hear her soulful voice again. According to Matthewman, they have “a bunch of songs” they are working on. “When we’re happy, then we’ll let everyone else hear it.”, he added. Read More: Thai cave boys speak of ‘miracle’ rescue after hospital discharge